</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udarthender.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DarthEnder</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/14/00 5:43:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousecontractsbountiesjobsquestsetc.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1898.topic&index=28>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: BITE... BITE... BITE...</span><hr size=1> I've said this elsewhere but it applies here.<br>
<br>
I like the way traps are handled right now.  They way the traps are part of the zone.  There are only 2 things I would change about the traps.<br>
<br>
1.  Instead of having traps going off constantly and revealing their location, make them only go off when walked into.  All other times, have the crusher retracted into the ceiling or the swinging axe into the wall etc.<br>
<br>
2.  They need effects besides breaking sneak and hide.  Some possible effects include:<br>
<br>
Alarm: agro all nearby mobs<br>
<br>
DD:  Does physical damage<br>
<br>
Poison:  Causes DoT.<br>
<br>
Magical effects:  Pretty much anything you can think of.  Blind, snare, stun.  All that fun stuff.<br>
<br>
As far as how the actual disarming works, I think two things should be implemented.<br>
<br>
1.  Sneaking characters will not trigger traps.  If a trap can't be seen, and can only be &quot;sensed&quot; with sense trap, then it's important that a sneaking character be able to walk into trigger range without setting off the trap.<br>
<br>
2.  Require &quot;Thief Tools&quot; to be in hand.  I've thought about this for a while, and I think that if we have to have lockpicks to pick locks, tools should be nessecary to disarm trap.  Require them to be in hand just like lockpicks.  And if you want to maintain simplicity, you can simply rename lockpicks as &quot;Thief Tool&quot; and use them for both, using the assumption that a thieving kit would contain lockpicks anyway.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
In any case, I would not want trap to be like mobs.  But I could live with it.<br>
<br>
What I could not stand would be random trap spawns.  Dungeons do not have random mob spawns(locations) because of the chaos it would cause.  This applies to traps as well. <p><img src="http://www.geocities.com/dboulais_1999/Thief03.jpg">
